Comment: Shortened the proofs of Proposition 2.8 and Theorem 3.15; modified
  Lemma 3.11; added Remark 3.6, Lemma 4.10, and Lemma 4.11; minor typos fixed;
  improved exposition; updated references

Comment: 8 pages, 14 figures (pagination changed in arXiv version); accepted
  for the International Conference on Intelligent Robots and Systems (IROS)
  2016

  I present here another example of a lattice fibration, a discrete version of
the highest dimensional Hopf fibration: $S^{7}\longrightarrow S^{15}
\longrightarrow S^{8}$.

  A new upper bound is given for the dimension of the space of holomorphic cusp
forms of weight one and prime level $q$: $$ \hbox{dim}\, S_1(q) << q^{11/12}
\log^4{q} $$ with an absolute implied constant.

